      <div class="seo-concept-faq-list reveal">
        <details class="seo-concept-faq-item" open>
          <summary>What is the difference between brand design and brand strategy?</summary>
          <p>Brand design is how you look; brand strategy is why you matter and how you win. We focus on the strategy first—positioning and narrative—before any visual execution happens.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>How long does a typical strategy project take?</summary>
          <p>A foundational project takes 4 weeks. A full 'Market Leader' overhaul typically spans 6-8 weeks, including deep research, workshops, and documentation of all messaging frameworks.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>Do we need strategy if we already have a logo?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. A logo is just a symbol. Strategizing your positioning and voice is what makes that symbol mean something to your customers and stand out from competitors.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>How do you research our competitors?</summary>
          <p>We use tools like BuzzSumo and BrandWatch combined with manual 'secret shopper' audits to understand their messaging, weaknesses, and where your unique opportunity lies.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>What deliverables do we receive at the end?</summary>
          <p>You receive a comprehensive Brand Strategy Deck including your Positioning Statement, Messaging Pillars, Customer Personas, Voice & Tone Guidelines, and a 12-month Growth Roadmap.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item seo-concept-faq-item">
          <summary>How do we measure the ROI of brand strategy?</summary>
          <p>We track metrics like Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC) reduction, increased sales close rates, higher customer lifetime value (LTV), and brand sentiment lift.</p>
        </details>
